@1262  = ~You must lead a lonely existence, mercenary. Those who hack a road through life with the sword of violence are doomed to find themselves awash in blood and misery at the end of their days.~
@1263  = ~Whatever. Tell me what you know about the Heartstone Gem.~
@1264  = ~Yeah, yeah. Do you know anything about the evil that has recently come to Kuldahar?~
@1265  = ~Kill them? No, no, my violent young friend. We Eldathyn are devoted to peace. It is not a confinement on our lives... it is a liberation. We would rather die than harm our cousins in the caves above.~
@1266  = ~That's *really* stupid.~
@1267  = ~Such devotion is truly admirable.~
@1268  = ~Hmm. Have you ever heard of the Heartstone Gem, the magical life-giving relic from Kuldahar? We're looking for it.~
@1269  = ~Oh. I don't suppose you know anything about a powerful source of evil that has come to reside in Kuldahar Pass, do you?~
@1270  = ~We don't expect everyone to see things the way we do. Is there anything else I can help you with?~
@1271  = ~Yes. Can you tell me what you know about the Heartstone Gem?~
@1272  = ~Sure. We're trying to locate the source of some powerful evil that has been stirring in Kuldahar. A lot of people have been abducted. We found of some of them in the caverns above, but we still don't know what's behind everything.~
@1273  = ~No. I can't deal with such blockheaded religious stupidity. Farewell.~
@1274  = ~It's like second nature to us, really. It is a very satisfying way of life. Is there anything else I can help you with?~
@1275  = ~Yes. Can you tell me what you know about the Heartstone Gem?~
@1276  = ~Sure. We're trying to locate the source of some powerful evil that has been stirring in Kuldahar. A lot of people have been abducted. We found of some of them in the caverns above, but we still don't know what's behind everything.~
@1277  = ~No, thanks. I must be going now.~
@1278  = ~Hello again. What can Albion do for you, my friend?~
@1279  = ~Are you sure you don't know anything about the Heartstone Gem?~
@1280  = ~Stunned~
@1281  = ~Where is the healer located?~
@1282  = ~Nothing, thanks. I must be going now.~
@1283  = ~Yes, I'm quite certain. I've heard legends about its powers, of course, but I don't know who stole it from the Temple of the Forgotten God.~
@1284  = ~Uh, Albion... I never told you that the gem was stolen from the Temple of the Forgotten God.~
@1285  = ~Where is the healer located?~
@1286  = ~Hmm. Okay. Thanks anyway. Farewell.~
@1287  = ~She is located to the east. Simply go through the large door behind me and take the hallway until you can turn right. She's through the first door on your left after that. Take care to not wander too far. Our inner sanctum is closed to outsiders.~
@1288  = ~Are you sure you don't know anything about the Heartstone Gem?~
@1289  = ~Thanks for your help, Albion. Farewell.~
@1290  = ~Oh... well, it's a local legend, you know. I heard it from one of the natives.~
@1291  = ~No... no. If my memory is correct, Arundel told me that very few people even knew that the Temple of the Forgotten God actually existed. It seems unlikely that any random native would have told you that the Heartstone Gem was there.~
@1292  = ~Belt~
@1293  = ~Hmm. Okay. Thanks, Albion. Farewell.~
@1294  = ~Ah. Arundel, Arundel. Why did that tree-loving fool have to get involved with this? He will hang by his entrails on his precious tree once we are finished with him. As for you, my friend... your inquisitive tongue will soon be ripped from your fat head. You will not stand in the way of my clan's return to power. *None* will oppose us!~
@1295  = ~What in the Nine Hells are you talking about, Albion?!~
@1296  = ~Yeah, that's what I thought. I knew you were a liar the first time I talked to you.~
@1297  = ~You had me going there for a moment, Albion. Good effort. You lose.~
@1298  = ~Hello again. What can Albion do for you, my friend?~
@1299  = ~Albion, can you tell me what in the Nine Hells is going on around here? I've seen some pretty odd things walking through your "den of peace," friend.~
@1300  = ~I was wondering if you could tell me about some of the things I've seen in your sanctuary.~
@1301  = ~Nothing. I'm fine. Farewell.~
@1302  = ~Oh dear! What sorts of things?~
@1303  = ~I found some books on your shelves that had some pretty strange titles. Are "How to Serve Man" and "Ophidian Necromancy" standard texts in Eldathyn monasteries?~
@1304  = ~I was looking at some of your carpets, the red and gold ones. They are quite exotic for an Eldathyn retreat. What do the gold carp on them symbolize?~
@1305  = ~One of the rooms to the north, it smells like someone died in there.~
@1306  = ~No, no. Not in Eldathyn monasteries. However, they are quite common in hidden yuan-ti temples to Sseth.~
@1307  = ~Hidden yuan-ti temples to Sseth? Heh, I suppose. But where are you going to find one of those around... hey!~
@1308  = ~A servant of the god of serpents masquerading as the head of an Eldathyn retreat. What are you planning on doing now, Albion?~
@1309  = ~Hmm. I think I'll be going now. Farewell, Albion.~
@1310  = ~They symbolize rising strength, a return to power. They mark the ascension of my clan to primacy in this world. It has taken us thousands of years to reach this position. Now that you have your answer, meddling buffoon, my kin and I will have to annihilate you.~
@1311  = ~What?! I just wanted to know about the fish, you crazy bastard!~
@1312  = ~Yeah, that's what I thought. I knew there was something weird about you the moment I set eyes on you. So it turns out you're part of some strange cult. No big surprise to me.~
@1313  = ~Uh, Albion, what are you talking about?~
@1314  = ~Someone did die in there. Many, many people died in there. Now that you have chosen to poke your head into our affairs, you will be the next humanoid to have the honor of dying in that room.~
@1315  = ~Huh?~
@1316  = ~Oh yeah, and I suppose you're going to be the one to do it, right, old man? What are you going to do... turn into a snake or something?~
@1317  = ~Heh. Good one, Albion. I didn't think Eldathyn had a sense of humor.~
@1318  = ~Have you ever been afraid of snakes, little one? Have you ever trembled at the sound of his hiss? You are afraid because you recognize a master race. Long before your kind danced on these lands, my people ruled on high! It shall be that way again, humanoid! All shall bask in the glory of Sseth! None shall stand against Yxunomei, his princess! Ah ha ha ha ha!~
@1319  = ~I still have no idea what you're talking about.~
@1320  = ~I'll stand against you, madman. You're obviously behind the abduction of the Heartstone Gem. Don't think you can stop me from finding it.~
@1321  = ~I certainly won't stand against you, Albion. However, I do think I'll be leaving now...~
@1322  = ~Slaughter! Blood and slaughter! Take the flesh of the unbelievers and roast it upon a pit of flame! Serve their hearts to Yxunomei, our princess! Devour them! Devour them in the name of Sseth, the Sibilant Death!~
@1323  = ~Interlopers, you should *never* have come here. I don't know what harm you've already done to my kin, but you will pay for it when we twist your flesh into a histachii breeding machine.~
@1324  = ~Welcome to our gathering, my friend. Would you care for a bite to eat? We were just beginning our dinnertime prayer...~
@1325  = ~Sure! There's nothing I like more than a quick bite of Kuldahar villager.~
@1326  = ~You monsters! How dare you commit this heinous act?~
@1327  = ~Eat up; I don't care. However, if you could take some time before eating to hand over the Heartstone Gem, I'd appreciate it.~
@1328  = ~No thanks. I was just leaving, really.~
@1329  = ~Blessed Sseth, face of Sch'theraqpasstt, thank you for blessing us with the arrival of bountiful sacks of meat, warm and full of precious wine.~
@1330  = ~Heh. I was just... uh... you know... kidding about the... thing and the uh... stuff...~
@1331  = ~Enough of your words, vile monster! I will listen to your mockery no more.~
@1332  = ~I think it's time for me to go.~
@1333  = ~We *dare* because we do not *fear*. Our god is strong and powerful, his handmaiden is as swift and terrible as lightning. The power of our clan has been waning for thousands of years. Our moon is waxing now, and it is as red as the blood of your weak and feeble kin, my friend.~
@1334  = ~That certainly *sounds* impressive... but do you have the guts to back it up?~
@1335  = ~I've listened to enough of your madness. I won't let you harm another innocent.~
@1336  = ~Please don't devour me. Just let me leave.~
@1337  = ~My friend, even if I were in possession of that item, I would not give it to you. It is a tool of our leader, Yxunomei. Revel in the glory of your death! The ritual of your kind's destruction marks the setting of your sun and the rising of Sseth's black star.~
@1338  = ~You will do no such thing. I will not let you continue with this insanity any longer.~
@1339  = ~Everyone has to have a dream, I suppose. Too bad you're about to wake up with my fist in your scaly face.~
@1340  = ~We spoke with Kresselack's spirit, and he claims he is not responsible for the evil that plagues Kuldahar, but he knows who is... since we had already slain the Aurilite priestess that he wished dead, he was willing to share his knowledge with us. Unfortunately, all Kresselack could tell me was that neither he nor anyone in the Vale of Shadows was responsible for the evil plaguing Kuldahar. It seems we will need to go back to Arundel and inform him of this. Perhaps he will have a clue as to what we should do next.~
@1341  = ~Look... I don't care about your plans. Just let me continue on my way.~
@1342  = ~Oh no, my friend! Not until you have felt the warm, tight embrace of our lord Sseth! Come closer... closer...~
@1343  = ~Do you require a demonstration of our power, my friends? I will grant you one right now, and it will be as bold and terrifying as any dark dream you have ever slept through. For the terrible majesty of Sseth!~
@1344  = ~Infidels! How dare you profane our summoning chamber! This holy place is reserved for those of *high class* and solemn bearing. You will suffer greatly for your vile, corrupting intrusion into our domain!~
@1345  = ~No, it is *you* who will suffer, monster!~
@1346  = ~You know what? You're not scaring me.~
@1347  = ~Sorry about the intrusion. I'll just close the door on my way out...~
@1348  = ~I don't think so. Your cowardice sickens me. Your pathetic gods granted you the blessing of a backbone. It is clear to me now that you unholy wretches have degenerated to the point where you don't even have that. No scales, no tail, no backbone, no purpose... truly a wretched form of "life." I will put you out of your misery.~
@1349  = ~We found the priestess of Auril that Kresselack spoke of, a woman named Lysan. Once she revealed herself, we attacked her.~
@1350  = ~Ah. A visitor. Stay still for a moment. I can't see you clearly. My eyes are no longer strong. Have you come as a student or a patient?~
@1351  = ~Uh... what?~
@1352  = ~A student, of course.~
@1353  = ~Patient.~
@1354  = ~Student or patient... it's a simple question.~
@1355  = ~For what purpose?~
@1356  = ~I'm a student.~
@1357  = ~I'm a patient.~
@1358  = ~Excellent! Yxunomei finally listened to my requests. Now, children, if you are to become truly cultured in our society, you must learn the fine vocation that I learned over a thousand years ago. It is the most graceful, demanding art that our society has produced.~
@1359  = ~And what, exactly, is this art?~
@1360  = ~I'm sure it is, you reptilian monster. Die!~
@1361  = ~Can you excuse me for a moment? I'll be right back.~
@1362  = ~Ah. More hypnotized candidates from the baptist. Perhaps you will possess some of the knowledge we are looking for. Lie down on that table while I get out my instruments. I only hope you last a bit longer than your friends. Humanoids are such fragile creatures.~
@1363  = ~djfshd~
@1364  = ~We'll see who's weak, fiend.~
@1365  = ~Sure, just hold on a second...~
@1366  = ~Need you ask?~
@1367  = ~Well... yes.~
@1368  = ~Of course not. I'm a student.~
@1369  = ~No. I'm a patient.~
@1370  = ~Torture, of course. It is the method by which our people have gathered information for thousands of years. When purebloods like you are few or ineffective, we must rely on much more direct means for learning about our foes.~
@1371  = ~Only creatures as vile as you would ever think of torture as an art.~
@1372  = ~Sure... I guess.~
@1373  = ~Yeah! That's what I've always thought, too. Torture's great.~
@1374  = ~Damn these weak eyes for failing me! No matter. You will suffer all the same, weaklings.~
@1375  = ~Wait... wait... something about you doesn't seem right... Impostors! Impostors! Damn my eyes for failing me!~
@1376  = ~Peoplesss! What are you doing? Cave belong to Lizard King Lissspen. Me.~
@1377  = ~It belongs to the Lizard King, eh? How did you come to own it?~
@1378  = ~This cave is going to belong to Dead Lizard King unless you tell me what your people are doing here.~
@1379  = ~Did you take the villagers away from the valley?~
@1380  = ~Where did you learn to speak Common, you ignorant savage? I've seen idiotic goblins with better speech than you.~
@1381  = ~Whoops. I didn't realize this was your cave. I'll be leaving now. Farewell.~
@1382  = ~Yxunomei bring us here. She call us.~
@1383  = ~Who is she? Is she your queen? What do you mean she "calls you"?~
@1384  = ~I think I hear her calling me, too. Farewell.~
@1385  = ~Proud peoples should no be ssso proud in presenccce of Lizard King. Lizard King are brave warrior many woundsss. Many human heartsss eaten after battle. Continue proud talk if wanting to have heart eaten.~
@1386  = ~I'd like to see you try, you scaly abomination.~
@1387  = ~I apologize, Lizard King. Please grant me some of your great wisdom.~
@1388  = ~No, uh... no heart eating today, thank you. I have to be getting back to civilization now. Farewell.~
@1389  = ~We take some for Yxunomei. Others taken for food.~
@1390  = ~The village? You're eating the villagers?! What kind of monsters are you?~
@1391  = ~Well, that makes sense to me. Human flesh *is* pretty tasty, after all.~
@1392  = ~Who is she? Is she your queen?~
@1393  = ~Lizard King are sssmart as you, idiot. Common not the wordsss of my people. Like to sssee you try ssspeaking lizard tongue.~
@1394  = ~I apologize, Lizard King. Please grant me some of your great wisdom.~
@1395  = ~You're pretty touchy, aren't you? I was just going anyway. Farewell.~
@1396  = ~Yxunomei not our queen. She queen of the sssnakesss. Lizard King do Yxunomei'sss tasksss to get food for hisss people. Village providesss usss much food.~
@1397  = ~The village? You're eating the villagers?!~
@1398  = ~Well, that makes sense to me. Human flesh *is* pretty tasty, after all.~
@1399  = ~Hmm. Interesting. Well, have fun with those villagers. I need to be going now. Farewell.~
@1400  = ~Yesss, yesss. Abominationsss. If you only knew my tasssty friends. Lizard King grow tired of playing with food now. Your time hasss come.~
@1401  = ~Giving praise to Lizard King not make me want eating you any lesss. Do not ssstruggle.~
@1402  = ~Lizard King not let you leave. People ssstarving, need food. You understand, yesss? Hold ssstill...~
@1403  = ~Lizard people ssstarving. Lizard King mussst make thingsss right and ssserve Yxunomei to help hisss people. You interfere. Cannot allow thisss.~
@1404  = ~Ha ha. You funny, try trick Lizard King. I eat you anyway. Not ssso funny now, is it? Sssorry, funny perssson.~
@1405  = ~We kind of monsters eat people because you tasty. Hold still...~
