@4626  = ~The name's Conlan. I'm the local smithy of these here parts. If ye're needin' a sharp blade or stout mace, I'm the man to see. Best take advantage while I'm still here.~
@4627  = ~by name~
@4628  = ~by date~
@4629  = ~~
@4630  = ~Aye, I suppose so. With all the skullduggery that's been goin' on around here, I imagine I'll not be around much longer.~
@4631  = ~I see. So you're planning on leaving town.~
@4632  = ~You're leaving Kuldahar? That doesn't surprise me... this town IS rather dull. Perhaps I could accompany you?~
@4633  = ~Ha! I wish that were possible. The southern pass has long since been snowed-in by this damnable weather we've been having lately. Now I hear tell that even the northern route to the Ten Towns has been blocked by an avalanche. Mark my words; none of us will last through this winter. We're all done for.~
@4634  = ~I have no intention of dying here. Why is it that you are so ready to line your own grave?~
@4635  = ~~
@4636  = ~Cheerful thought. May I see what you have for sale?~
@4637  = ~Well, it's been... nice talking to you. Farewell.~
@4638  = ~Humph. Not much for me to live for, really. My Mary passed a few years ago from the fever. And now... now my son's gone missin', snatched out of his bed in the middle of the night—right out from under my nose! He was just a boy!~
@4639  = ~I'm sorry, Conlan. Any idea who or what took him?~
@4640  = ~[no text]~
@4641  = ~That's unfortunate. Would you mind showing me what weapons you have for sale?~
@4642  = ~Hmm. The little brat probably just ran away. I would've run away too if my father were such a depressing bore.~
@4643  = ~Sure, kick a man when he's down. I hope you feel better now. Now, if you don't mind, I've got work that needs doin'. Go torment someone else.~
@4644  = ~If I knew that, do you think I'd be standin' around here poundin' at metal? He just vanished, I tell you. Gone without a trace. Even ol' Arundel couldn't find a trail, and he's got a nose for such things. I imagine whatever took him will come back for me next. I can't say it'll be unwelcome.~
@4645  = ~Who is this Arundel?~
@4646  = ~CHARACTER~
@4647  = ~I've spoken with Arundel. He believes the source of the disturbances may lie within the Vale of Shadows.~
@4648  = ~You have my sympathy, Conlan. Perhaps you can show me what blades you have so I might arm myself against the likes of the rogues that abducted your son.~
@4649  = ~Kerish, the frost salamander leader, has asked us to return the escaped slaves to him or slay them. We agreed to do this.~
@4650  = ~[no text]~
