@5379  = ~I will see to it this blade is returned to Jhonen, Elisia.~
@5380  = ~::Here, then, I entrust this to your keeping until your path crosses with that of Jho-nyn.:: ::Return when you have given it to him.:: ::I must know if it has found its way back to its home.::~
@5381  = ~I'll return when I've given it to Jhonen, Elisia. Farewell.~
@5382  = ~[no text]~
@5383  = ~[no text]~
@5384  = ~::I mean no harm upon Jho-nyn.::~
@5385  = ~Ah, I did not ask about your intentions, I asked about the *gift*—you've said nothing of what it may do. As for no harm upon Jhonen, well, your dreams are already hurting him, whether you mean them to or not.~
@5386  = ~::The dreams were the only way I could speak to him.:: ::The blade is for him.:: ::I only wish him to dwell in the waves beside me.:: ~
@5387  = ~[XZAR 39]~ [XZARR39]
@5388  = ~But humans can't *live* beneath the waves, Elisia. For your kind, you are obviously headstrong to appear upon the shores here where anyone may see you. That speaks to me a desperate heart. And a desperate heart does dangerous things.~
@5389  = ~[YESLICK 12]~ [YESLK12]
@5390  = ~[YESLICK 13]~ [YESLK13]
@5391  = ~[YESLICK 16]~ [YESLK16]
