@8146  = ~"Idiots! Get those chickens!"~
@8147  = ~"Blix, get over there!"~
@8148  = ~"Move it!"~
@8149  = ~"Help him, Kreg!"~
@8150  = ~Defilers! Again you profane this temple with your murderous presence!~
@8151  = ~Silence! Think you that the children of the Forgotten God are fools enough to be deceived by such lies twice in one day? Now you shall pay for your trespasses! Guards! Guards! The intruders have returned!~
@8152  = ~There is no mistake! The bodies of my slain brothers are not even cold, and yet more intruders arrive... no doubt to finish us off. Well, you'll find that this time we shall not fall so easily! Guards! Guards! The intruders have returned!~
@8153  = ~So, you admit you are thieves! Well, you'll find that this time we shall not fall so easily! Guards! Guards! The intruders have returned!~
@8154  = ~There must be some mistake... we've never set foot in this temple before now.~
@8155  = ~Calm yourself, friend. We mean you no harm. We've come from the beleaguered town of Kuldahar on a mission of great importance.~
@8156  = ~Stand aside, priest. We've come for the Heartstone Gem.~
@8157  = ~Staff of Command~
@8158  = ~I didn't realize your kind COULD speak.~
@8159  = ~start over~
@8160  = ~I'm sorry, but I really must be on my way.~
@8161  = ~Greetings... again, traveler.~
@8162  = ~I have disposed of the orog chieftain and acquired his badge.~
@8163  = ~How is it that you are speaking to me?~
@8164  = ~~
@8165  = ~I'm just passing by.~
@8166  = ~I... am not what... you see. I... was a master... transmuter. A red... wizard of Thay. My knowledge... vast and... aruu...~
@8167  = ~Helm of Brilliance~
@8168  = ~You were a wizard?~
@8169  = ~Skull of Death~
@8170  = ~How is it that you came to be in your current form?~
@8171  = ~I'm sorry, but I don't have the patience for this. Good day.~
@8172  = ~My name... is... was Saablic... Tan. Of my... mistakes... one grew tired... used my precious... magics to make... that which... I am. Having... much confusion as... days move on. Must... mm... tell you I... am frightened.~
@8173  = ~Why are you frightened?~
@8174  = ~~
@8175  = ~Orogs that... roam these passages... my passages... are my... creation. They... have much contempt... for me. I cannot... leave. My form... my home... punishment for my... ambition. I... derived pleasure... for altering against... their will. I have... much regret.~
@8176  = ~How can the situation be rectified?~
@8177  = ~Why should anyone feel sorry for you?~
@8178  = ~I will leave you to your regrets.~
@8179  = ~Pearly White Ioun Stone~
@8180  = ~What is done... is done. I cannot... excuse my actions... or my... intents. I am... not alone in... guilt and I... am consumed with... hatred for one. Responsibility... rests not... on my soul... alone. I am... but a pawn.~
@8181  = ~Ioun Stone~
@8182  = ~Dusty Rose Ioun Stone~
@8183  = ~Pale Green Ioun Stone~
@8184  = ~Dragon Helm~
@8185  = ~Tell me more of your situation.~
@8186  = ~I've heard enough and must be on my way.~
@8187  = ~I must... be brief as... I grow tired. You can... help others... and help me. Within... these caves... the orogs have... a leader. Not only... that role... but another he... fills.~
@8188  = ~What is this other role?~
@8189  = ~He is one... of six. His presence... and others... here to prevent... intrusion. Placed... by the one... that would wrong... myself and many... many others. Without... his existence... his minions will... scatter... and the evil... drow weaker.~
@8190  = ~You want me to dispose of this leader?~
@8191  = ~I believe I already disposed of this leader.~
@8192  = ~Mandolin~
@8193  = ~I'm afraid... there may be... no other way. I remain... overcome... with guilt. I... cannot excuse... my actions however... my relevance... in this world... flickers and a... far greater injustice... burns bright.~
@8194  = ~I will see what I can do.~
@8195  = ~I won't do that. Farewell.~
@8196  = ~Mandolin of Marvelous Preservation~
@8197  = ~I... am very... grateful and know... your actions extend... beyond my... plight. Before you... leave... he will be... in possession of... a symbol. A... badge. You must obtain... this. Return with... this and I... will know you... are true to... your word. I will... attempt to provide... more insight then.~
@8198  = ~I will return.~
@8199  = ~~
@8200  = ~I am... forever in debt... to you. I... cannot speak much... longer. I must... tell you that... each of the six... have such a... badge. Should you... go in search of... him you will... need to obtain... each of them. I... must... rest.~
@8201  = ~Goodbye, Saablic.~
@8202  = ~Know this... traveler. Without... my knowledge... your continued existence... within this world... will be limited.~
@8203  = ~All right, I'm listening.~
@8204  = ~I'll take my chances.~
@8205  = ~Thank you... again, traveler. I must... rest.~
@8206  = ~Can I ask...~
@8207  = ~You're welcome, Saablic.~
