@8353  = ~Frostbite~
@8354  = ~Adventurers? Here in the Hand of the Seldarine? You must have fought past the horde below. Battle ready, I take it? Tell me, why are you here?~
@8355  = ~We seek to find Larrel. Evil stalks the land, and we need his powers to find the source.~
@8356  = ~~
@8357  = ~Very battle ready, I might add. More than adequate to deal with another ghost if she thinks to attack us.~
@8358  = ~We seek Larrel, the only one who can summon forth the divining power of the Heartstone Gem.~
@8359  = ~A noble cause. That's something my heart has yearned for—what I wouldn't give to ride once again for such causes. Well met, adventurers. My name is Kaylessa. I am... was... the weapons master of the Hand.~
@8360  = ~A hearty lot you are! It's good to see the fighting spirit still alive after so many decades. That same spirit used to drive all my thoughts and actions... before the fall. My name is Kaylessa. I am... was... the weapons master of the Hand.~
@8361  = ~~
@8362  = ~Hmmm. I don't know much about this Heartstone Gem, but it must be powerful indeed if only Larrel can use its powers. My name is Kaylessa. I am... was... the weapons master of the Hand.~
@8363  = ~With that all said, you must have some questions that need answering.~
@8364  = ~Well met, Kaylessa. We would know more about you—you're very different from most of the spirits we've encountered here.~
@8365  = ~Ulraunt~
@8366  = ~As we had mentioned, we need to find Larrel. Can you help us?~
@8367  = ~Unfortunately my questions will have to wait for now. Farewell, Kaylessa.~
@8368  = ~When the Hand was at the pinnacle of its glory, I trained my people in the ways of combat. No one could best my deftness with the sword or my accuracy with the bow.~
@8369  = ~All my soldiers were honed to perfection. When we were called to battle, it did not take long before our enemies found their forces in chaos and retreat.~
@8370  = ~Those days are long gone now. Any of my soldiers that remain are twisted shadows of their former selves. I differ from them only in that I have retained my senses. It is a curse, knowing what we've become and powerless to do anything about it.~
@8371  = ~Kaylessa, I'd like to talk about how to find Larrel. Perhaps something can be done to help you if we find him.~
@8372  = ~You have my sympathies, Kaylessa. Farewell.~
@8373  = ~Finding Larrel will not be easy. When the Hand fell, he was damned. He is now a Baelnorn, an elven lich-like creature doomed to live forever. How this came about? I do not know.~
@8374  = ~You may have seen Larrel as you have explored the Hand, but what you saw is not truly him—it is more a "sending," a figment of himself that wanders the Hand. Larrel—the true Larrel—is atop Labelas Tower.~
@8375  = ~Every time I have seen Larrel's sending, it has rambled on like a village idiot—with one exception. Once, it mentioned something about Larrel's great astrolabe and how it was no longer turning.~
@8376  = ~Can you tell me more about Larrel's astrolabe?~
@8377  = ~Kaylessa, I have other questions for you.~
@8378  = ~Very interesting. I must depart for now.~
@8379  = ~Larrel's astrolabe is a wondrous device constructed to help him and his wizards research space and time. As I recall, Larrel and his wizards were using it during the last days of the Hand.~
@8380  = ~In the aftermath of the Hand's destruction, I found this piece of machinery, which I believe to be a piece of Larrel's astrolabe. After seeing the state of mind of most everyone left in the Hand, I have held onto it and guarded it. The last thing I wanted was someone using the power held within this piece to cause further harm to the Hand.~
@8381  = ~Kaylessa, we may need that item if we are to have Larrel help us.~
@8382  = ~I'd like to ask some other questions.~
@8383  = ~Many thanks for your time. Farewell.~
@8384  = ~You have been cursed with petrification.~
@8385  = ~Your intentions may be noble, but I'm afraid I cannot entrust you with this item yet. You will need to prove yourselves first.~
@8386  = ~How?~
@8387  = ~The elves atop this tower were among my most dedicated soldiers. Whatever curse befell the Hand not only twisted their bodies, but twisted their minds as well. They act and live as if in the final moments of the Hand. Forever prepared to defend against any intrusion to this tower.~
@8388  = ~What of them?~
@8389  = ~My soldiers do not deserve what has befallen them—they deserve to die in battle. They would want to meet their end with steel in their hands upon the battlefield. I would ask that you climb the tower and send them to eternal rest.~
@8390  = ~I will put them to rest as you wish.~
@8391  = ~Let me think about it. Farewell.~
@8392  = ~You have my heartfelt thanks. Return to me when my soldiers are at peace.~
@8393  = ~I see you have returned, adventurers.~
@8394  = ~Greetings once again, Kaylessa. You had mentioned you were the Hand's weapon master?~
@8395  = ~We still seek to find Larrel. Can you help us?~
@8396  = ~Kaylessa, your soldiers all fought with great honor. Their suffering has ended, and they rest now.~
@8397  = ~Good to see you, Kaylessa. I must depart.~
@8398  = ~I thank you for helping with one of my last tasks in this realm. Before I give you your reward, I would have you help me one last time. With my soldiers at rest, there is only one thing left for me to do—to join them. I would ask for the honor of dying in battle.~
@8399  = ~Kaylessa, I have already encountered your soldiers on the upper levels. They all fought with great honor. They rest in peace now.~
@8400  = ~White Wyrm~
@8401  = ~Greetings, SAH! Welcome! Welcome! Don't be taken back by all the wonderful items I have for sale. Come! Come! My name is Lehland, and I'm the proprietor of this establishment.~
@8402  = ~Well met. I am called <GABBER>. No insult intended but your "establishment" doesn't seem to be able to service anyone.~
@8403  = ~Lehland, I'd like to browse some of your fine goods.~
@8404  = ~I don't understand. Why do you tend shop in this destroyed fortress? The Severed Hand was destroyed hundreds of years ago.~
@8405  = ~Surely you jest, SAH! Why my store has some of the FINEST wares from across the land! Just look around! Look at that rug hanging on the west wall. Quality of this caliber can only be found from the far reaches of the east.~
@8406  = ~Hmmm, perhaps you can show me some of your other quality wares.~
@8407  = ~Can you tell me about the elves of the Hand?~
@8408  = ~I see. I think I'll come back and check your selection then. Farewell.~
@8409  = ~Have you been sipping too much elven wine, SAH? The *Severed Hand*? What in Corellon's name is that, SAH? Is that what you southerners call the Hand of the Seldarine? Destroyed? SAH, I do not mean to be insulting, but if you look outside my store, you will see many elves, alive and well, going about their daily business.~
@8410  = ~Tell me about the other elves in the Hand.~
@8411  = ~I'd like to see those finer goods you were speaking of.~
@8412  = ~I think *you're* the one that's been hitting the elven wine.~
@8413  = ~Uh, I think I'll go see what they're doing myself. Be well, Lehland.~
@8414  = ~Of course, SAH! As you have probably noticed, The Hand of the Seldarine is more of a fortress. We are always in constant preparation for battle against the dark horde of the North. As you have seen, the levels below house the majority of the elven forces.~
@8415  = ~SAH! I would kindly ask you to take your business elsewhere until you can speak in a more civilized manner! Good day.~
@8416  = ~Farewell, Lehland.~
@8417  = ~Some would call Corellon Tower the place where many, if not all, of the important decisions are made regarding the Ar'Tel'Quessir of the North. As of late, most of our time has been spent in preparing a defense against the horde—almost as if the fight was going to be taken to our front door. But fear not, SAH! The Ar'Tel'Quessir of the North will crush the Horde long before their feet touch this fortress.~
@8418  = ~Tell me about Shevarash Tower.~
@8419  = ~Can you tell me about Sehanine Tower?~
@8420  = ~I'm interested in hearing about Labelas Tower.~
@8421  = ~Solonor Tower—tell me what you know of it.~
@8422  = ~Can I see what you have for sale?~
@8423  = ~~
@8424  = ~In Shevarash Tower, you will find where the armed forces of the Ar'Tel'Quessir of the North train and equip themselves for battle. From blade to bow, Kaylessa takes every elf and hones them to do battle with the horde. Perhaps she can give you a few lessons as well, SAH.~
@8425  = ~Tell me about Corellon Tower.~
@8426  = ~Can you tell me about Sehanine Tower?~
@8427  = ~I'm interested in hearing about Labelas Tower.~
@8428  = ~Solonor Tower—tell me what you know of it.~
@8429  = ~Can I see what you have for sale?~
@8430  = ~~
@8431  = ~Deep within Sehanine Tower is where we enchant the weapons and armor used against the horde. It is one of our most heavily guarded towers to ensure that the craft as well as its items do not fall in the wrong hands. If that were to happen, it could easily turn the tide of the war against us.~
@8432  = ~~
