@8479  = ~I am looking for the orog chieftain.~
@8480  = ~Did you know that there's an Umber Hulk in these caves that used to be a Red Wizard of Thay?~
@8481  = ~Just passing through.~
@8482  = ~You have found him. What do you want?~
@8483  = ~I have come to obtain your badge.~
@8484  = ~I suggest you defend yourself.~
@8485  = ~You will get nothing, and you will die.~
@8486  = ~I beg to differ.~
@8487  = ~The wizard?! Where IS he?!~
@8488  = ~In these caves, just north of here.~
@8489  = ~Sorry, I can't tell you that.~
@8490  = ~You! You stay here while we kill him.~
@8491  = ~Okay.~
@8492  = ~Then you will die now.~
@8493  = ~I don't think so.~
@8494  = ~Nobody passes through. You die.~
@8495  = ~We'll see about that.~
@8496  = ~Thanks for your help, stranger. These beasts came out of nowhere. Watch your backs... there are more of them about.~
@8497  = ~Glad to be of help. Farewell.~
@8498  = ~You'd best hurry. Even as we speak, innocent folk are dying. These creatures must be stopped!~
@8499  = ~Farewell.~
@8500  = ~"RRRRRAAAAAARGH!!! Whre si my magic hatt??!!! I AM VARY DIPSLLEASED SIR!!! Ph34R M3!!!"~
@8501  = ~So, we meet again. Welcome to Cryshal-Tirith. I trust your visitation is not a social call.~
@8502  = ~Interesting choice of words. Much has changed since you last visited Easthaven. Now, as you can see, *I* run this town.~
@8503  = ~You insolent dog! How dare you speak to me in such a manner! I am Pomab Ak'azmhir, master of this tower and appointed ruler of Easthaven!~
@8504  = ~Poquelin? You still have no idea of what you are up against, do you? The master has many names... and many forms. His power is beyond imagination. You cannot hope to defeat him. Why not just surrender yourselves to me? At least I would be merciful and grant you a quick death.~
@8505  = ~It is the master's will that I should rule over this town. It was he who gave me this tower, this magnificent palace, as a reward for my service to him.~
@8506  = ~The occupation of Easthaven was inevitable. The master had intended to take the town from the very beginning. I was simply charged with removing certain obstacles so that his plans would go more smoothly.~
@8507  = ~Bathed-In-Blood +4~
@8508  = ~Jeffy~
@8509  = ~Kheros the Red wore this blood-red suit of plate mail through many of the years that he fought for the church of Tempus. He was born as the son of humble farmers near Calaunt. When he was a young man, he set off for the city to hire himself out as a mercenary. After a number of successful endeavors, Kheros became a short-term member of many adventuring companies. Along the way, despite his many victories, Kheros became disgusted and terrified by the sight of blood.

His fear eventually spiraled out of control, consuming him with madness. Priests of Tempus found the huge warrior and took him into safekeeping. The priests believed that they could cure Kheros of his fear. Over several years, Kheros learned the ways of the Tempuran religion, eventually becoming a priest. His final step in overcoming his fear was being submerged in a tub of blood until he almost drowned. All the time he was held down, he never struggled, flinched, or tried to escape. In his later years, he had a suit of armor made to remind him of his past.

STATISTICS:

Armor Class: -1 (-4 vs. slashing)
Requires:
 12 Strength

Weight: 55~
@8510  = ~This war hammer was enchanted by the church of Torm to return charmed wayward combatants to their standard allegiance. High priests of Torm typically held the hammer in battle, keeping an eye out for anyone who might be swayed to attack his or her comrades through magic. Redemption was lost when the last high priest to hold the weapon, Ardo Meller, was killed in the Battle of Black Lawns, 1230 DR. It is believed that agents of the draconic god Tchazzar dragged the weapon from the scene.

STATISTICS:

