@9241  = ~But we had no milk. It was the summertime. I remember it. Mother was dressed in a black dress, and the pious sun shone red upon us that day. All days are red now, and all the pretty ones are deep, deep in the black sea.~
@9242  = ~There was a porcelain vase sitting on the corner of the table. Father thought it strange, so strange to find the vase sitting there. He placed it under the table, in the blackness, to hide it from my eyes.~
@9243  = ~This priest is crying, mumbling prayers to Ilmater for forgiveness. He seems to not take notice of anything going on around him.~
@9244  = ~Welcome to our humble church, disciples of suffering. I am Brother Perdiem, servant of Ilmater. What brings you here today? Do you seek ecstasy at the hands of Ilmater's servants?~
@9245  = ~This temple doesn't seem like the place where kind, gentle gods are worshipped.~
@9246  = ~You do not do the work of Ilmater. This temple is a mockery of all that Ilmater stands for.~
@9247  = ~You do not do the work of Ilmater. This temple is a mockery of all that Ilmater stands for.~
@9248  = ~No, I do not seek ecstasy. I seek Revered Brother Poquelin.~
