@10580 = ~I enter battle tomorrow with a heavy heart, knowing I may well not survive. Such is life, and many a fool has risked as much for less gold than I will be paid. Still, I cannot bear the possibility of losing the treasures I have worked so hard for. To prevent this, I write this note to myself as a reminder in case I suffer an injury that would impair my faculties. Any battle against a mage always carries such a risk.

Quenash, my beautiful fallen saint, holds my cloak as a reminder of me. My helm I will trust only to my guile in hiding it. It rests where people rest, in a building that may as well have been named for the purpose. The cloak should be with it, but that would only be expected. I shall not make their theft easy.~
@10581 = ~Well, it certainly doesn't warrant Marketh beating you. Do you want me to take care of him for you?~
@10582 = ~Yes. It was wrong. Drow is gutter speech.~
@10583 = ~No! Please, don't. Whatever he's done, you must promise me you won't hurt him.~
@10584 = ~Okay. I promise I won't hurt him.~
@10585 = ~Sorry, I can't promise you anything.~
@10586 = ~No way. He's dead. Have no doubts about it, when I find him, it's over.~
@10587 = ~I should have seen it coming. I abused Malavon constantly while he was growing up. When Revered Brother Poquelin and his lieutenants met with my people, I slighted Marketh. I wouldn't speak to him because he was male. Instead, I spoke with Maiden Ilmadia. After long discussion, our city could find no reason to ally with Poquelin.~
@10588 = ~Unlike the rest of my people, Malavon wanted to join with the Revered Brother. I discovered this, so he abducted me and took me to Marketh for "safekeeping." They eventually found out anyway. Now Poquelin is planning some sort of assault on my former home. And I... I am left here with Marketh.~
@10589 = ~Squire Melvin~
@10590 = ~Do you want me to take care of Marketh for you?~
@10591 = ~Thank you. I understand why you're here. It has something to do with Poquelin, doesn't it? Listen, I know this will sound crazy, but I'm sure that Marketh could be a better person somehow if he could just get out of here.~
