@13929 = ~This tube is unpowered and the creature within is dead.~
@13930 = ~No, that's the tower of Orrick the Gray. Fortunate we are to have a wizard this far north. Friendlier than most spellcasters I've known; he values his privacy, but I still see him tip back a tankard or two with the best of them at the Root Cellar. He's got some goblin that does chores for him.~
@13931 = ~~
@13932 = ~~
@13933 = ~The Vale of Shadows? Might want to ask Mirek. He and his brother Silas make a pilgrimage there every year to pay their respects to their ancestors. I think they left on their trip a day or two ago, though, so they won't be back for a while.~
@13934 = ~I'll see if I can find them in the Vale, then.~
@13935 = ~I ran into Mirek. He was nearly killed by a pack of yetis that were prowling the Vale. I offered to go get a heirloom of his back.~
@13936 = ~I ran into Mirek. He was nearly killed by a pack of yetis that were prowling the Vale. I ended up going to fetch one of his family heirlooms back from a yeti that had swallowed it... and his brother.~
@13937 = ~So you're the one! Bravo indeed. Takes a braver one than me to face down one of those winter beasts.~
@13938 = ~Thanks. Can you tell me anything else about the Vale, especially the crypts?~
@13939 = ~Friend, don't go stepping foot into the Vale of Shadows—it's not a place for the living, and as long as the dead mind their own affairs, we mind ours.~
@13940 = ~I have to go there—the Vale may be the source of the troubles in Kuldahar.~
@13941 = ~Never been to the Vale of Shadows myself, but I've heard it's covered in shadows—it's like twilight there all the time. No good'll come from the living setting foot in the Vale. Let evil feed on evil, that's what I say.~
@13942 = ~There's not much choice. Any advice or information you could offer would be welcome.~
@13943 = ~Well, I don't know too much about the Vale—or even like talking about it, for that matter. You may have better luck with some of the other townsfolk. They may know more than I do, and there's no telling what random tidbit someone might cough up when you're talking with them.~
@13944 = ~~
@13945 = ~~
@13946 = ~You know, just last month, Gerth was going on about one of the tombs said to be in the Vale of Shadows—says one of them's the tomb of Kresselack the Black Wolf.~
@13947 = ~Kresselack? Don't think I've ever heard of him.~
@13948 = ~~
@13949 = ~~
@13950 = ~I'll ask some of the other townsfolk, then. Farewell.~
@13951 = ~Terrorized this region years ago, he did, with a whole legion of soldiers, shamans, and priests under his banner.~
@13952 = ~Priests? What kind of priests?~
@13953 = ~That's a good-sized force for this region. It'd take a man of some strength to lead such a band, especially if it had spellcasters in it.~
