@14993 = ~I'm just an aging soul who prefers the solitude of these mountains to the hustle and bustle of town life. I tell you, I've lived in this pass for years, and I've never seen *anything* like what just happened.~
@14994 = ~I know. I saw the whole thing. I was dozing off in my cave over yonder when I felt the ground begin to shake and heard a rumble something fierce. I stumbled outside just in time to see the avalanche come crashing down.~
@14995 = ~Yep. I saw the whole thing. I was sleeping in my cave over yonder when I felt the ground begin to shake and heard a rumble something fierce. I stumbled outside just in time to see the avalanche come crashing down.~
@14996 = ~It's a good thing you ran forward instead of back into the pass like the others. Poor bastards. One thing's for sure... I'm not digging their bodies out from under there. They'll have to wait 'til the snows melt to receive a proper burial.~
@14997 = ~Where you headed? It's obvious you can't go back the way you came.~
@14998 = ~Kuldahar? Why would you want to go to that miserable little berg? Nothing there but a big tree and a bunch of shacks and lean-tos. It's an eyesore, if you ask me.~
@14999 = ~Humph. A fool's errand. You'd be better off worrying about yourselves and leaving them *townsfolk* to deal with their own problems.~
