@16398 = ~Ah, yes. Terrible. Terrible. At first, there were tales told by travelers of companions disappearing into the night, snatched up from their bedrolls as they camped along the narrow trail that winds through the pass.~ [ARUN_15]
@16399 = ~Phased~
@16400 = ~We did not think much of these tales, for such occurrences are not unheard of in these mountains.~ [ARUN_16]
@16401 = ~Then one night Conlan's boy, Sheemish, went missing. The next morning, the whole town searched for the boy but turned up nothing. He was just gone. Vanished without a trace.~ [ARUN_17]
@16402 = ~"Those one-eyed brutes best stay clear of my tavern."~
