@21510 = ~I'm not going to leave.~
@21511 = ~I will leave now. Farewell.~
@21512 = ~I am a guardian spirit. My body was burned so I could protect this isle from your kind. I was the strongest of my family, so I am the leader of the spirits. Go now, or I will kill you.~
@21513 = ~Why do you want to destroy us?~
@21514 = ~~
@21515 = ~Very well. I will go. Farewell.~
@21516 = ~Your souls are diseased. Your presence on this island angers the dead. Leave now or I will tear you apart.~
@21517 = ~Is there anything we can do to make things right?~
@21518 = ~I'll leave when I want to, and not a moment sooner.~
@21519 = ~I will take my leave, then. Farewell.~
@21520 = ~If you will not leave, you will join the dead.~
@21521 = ~I do not know. I am a beast, gifted with speech to honor my strength. I protect this island from trespassers. Leave now.~
@21522 = ~I have business on this island. I will not leave until I have finished it.~
@21523 = ~~
@21524 = ~You have not left the island. For this, you must be killed.~
@21525 = ~Greetings, adventurers. I am... *cough* Edion. What brings you to the Burial Isle?~
@21526 = ~I am looking for a barbarian shaman named Hjollder. Have you seen him?~
@21527 = ~I am looking for someone... what are you doing on this island?~
@21528 = ~What's wrong? Are you sick?~
@21529 = ~Before I tell you anything, I want to know who *you* are.~
@21530 = ~My tasks are my concern. Farewell.~
@21531 = ~I am afraid not. Sorry to... *cough* disappoint you. A few nights ago, I did see a small boat land on the northeast tip of the island, but I do not know who was... *cough* in it.~
@21532 = ~~
@21533 = ~Although I sense no evil in your soul, your aura appears tainted with some sort of dark magic.~
@21534 = ~Thanks anyway. Farewell.~
@21535 = ~My name is Edion Caradoc. I live here on this... *cough* island. I am a fisherman.~
@21536 = ~You seem to be more than a fisherman, Edion.~
@21537 = ~~
@21538 = ~~
@21539 = ~Well met, Edion, but I must be leaving. Farewell.~
@21540 = ~Most perceptive. Yes, I am ill. *cough* *cough* It's been bothering me for about a year now, but it will end soon.~
@21541 = ~"End soon"? What do you mean?~
@21542 = ~~
@21543 = ~I must take my leave now, Edion. Farewell.~
@21544 = ~*cough* I was once a wizard... a necromancer. I was the ally of knights and kings in a nation far to the south. I was a part of many great and horrible adventures. That... *cough* that seems so long ago, now.~
@21545 = ~What happened?~
@21546 = ~~
@21547 = ~Three years ago, I was part of a struggle to protect Tethyr from a bleak cabal of... *cough* wizards and murderous thugs. Individually, they were not powerful. However, they were well organized and had access to devastating magical rituals.~
@21548 = ~What kind of rituals?~
@21549 = ~Interesting, but I have to leave now, Edion. Farewell.~
@21550 = ~The most powerful of these rituals was a ceremony that involved dozens of blood sacrifices and... *cough* days of arcane observances. They performed this ritual to eliminate me, the most direct threat to their ascendancy.~
@21551 = ~What was the result?~
@21552 = ~~
@21553 = ~I am infected by negative... *cough* *cough* energy, and there is no way to be rid of it short of divine intervention. Casting spells quickens the pace of the disease, causing... *cough* pain, rage, and eventually, death.~
@21554 = ~There isn't *any* way to cure the disease?~
@21555 = ~You're a necromancer, correct? Why not undergo the procedure to become a lich?~
@21556 = ~~
@21557 = ~I'm sorry to hear that, Edion. Farewell.~
@21558 = ~Only a deity has the power to cure my ailment. However, I am content to simply live out the rest of my days on this isle. The fish are... *cough* plentiful, the visitors are not, and it is a quiet place to die. Few men could ask for more at the end of their days.~
@21559 = ~So you're just going to let yourself die?~
@21560 = ~~
@21561 = ~~
@21562 = ~Farewell, Edion.~
@21563 = ~No, my friend... *cough* I cannot do that. I have spent my entire life manipulating the line between this world and the next. It is time for me to cross over that line. Death is the only antidote for my condition.~
@21564 = ~So you're just going to let yourself die?~
@21565 = ~You must have collected many magic items over the years, Edion. Would you be willing to part with any of them?~
@21566 = ~You must have quite a hoard of magic items hidden on this island. Why don't you hand them over?~
@21567 = ~What do you know about this island?~
@21568 = ~Very well. I must take my leave now, Edion. Farewell.~
@21569 = ~Death is change, but... *cough* it is not the end. Every man is responsible for his own life. I choose to let mine run its course. Do not worry about me. There are far more fish in this lake than there are sunsets left in my life.~
@21570 = ~~
@21571 = ~~
@21572 = ~~
@21573 = ~Yes, but I am far more... *cough* interested in buying magical weapons and armor than selling my magic items. The spirits on this island appreciate gifts in the form of a fine sword or a stout suit of armor.~
@21574 = ~Very well, let me see what you have.~
@21575 = ~I'm not interested in *buying* your items, Edion. Give them to me.~
@21576 = ~"The spirits on this island"? What do you know of them?~
@21577 = ~~
@21578 = ~*cough* *cough* If you think I am going to just hand over these items to you, you must think that stupidity is part of my condition.~
@21579 = ~Fine. Let me see what you have for sale.~
@21580 = ~If I can't persuade you to give me the items, I'll just have to use force. Farewell, Edion.~
@21581 = ~Hmm. Very well. What do you know about this island, Edion?~
@21582 = ~Well... *cough* the barbarians use this island to bury their heroes and chieftains. Most of them are buried... *cough* underground, but eventually, they ran out of room and they occasionally bury their heroes on the surface.~
@21583 = ~Recently, something happened on the island that angered the spirits. I believe it was caused by the appearance of an evil spirit on the island, but I cannot say for certain.~
@21584 = ~Is there anything that can be done to pacify the spirits?~
@21585 = ~Do you have any magic items hidden away that you would be willing to sell?~
@21586 = ~Thank you for your help. Farewell, Edion.~
@21587 = ~It is possible, but I... *cough* *cough* doubt it. The barbarians have very strong beliefs about sanctity. Once something or someone is "tainted" in their eyes, it is hard for it to be redeemed.~
@21588 = ~Would you be willing to tell us about your past, Edion?~
@21589 = ~~
@21590 = ~Would you be willing to tell us about your past, Edion?~
@21591 = ~~
@21592 = ~Welcome back, travelers. Is there anything you need?~
@21593 = ~Do you have any magic items I could look at?~
@21594 = ~No, nothing. Farewell, Edion.~
@21595 = ~*sigh* You have killed Young Ned, yes? You bloodthirsty idiots... *cough* *cough* I will not to wait to see what morbid plans you have for me. Farewell.~
@21596 = ~Jamison's Sling +4~
@21597 = ~A philosopher mage named Giddeon the Believer was the creator of this weapon. He claimed that there were natural "currents" of energy that existed throughout the world. To tap into the power behind these currents, Giddeon stated, a wizard simply needed to understand how they functioned. Once he or she understood the flow of energy, he or she could theoretically draw power from it through spellcasting or through a "focus device." When Giddeon's laboratory was destroyed by a colossal explosion in 1010 DR, this spear was one of the only items that survived. The spear guides itself along natural lines of energy as it veers towards its targets. Rarely, the spear will tap into a line of latent power and cause it to explode in a shaft of violent force.

