@21707 = ~Old Jed, the fisherman from Easthaven, is your uncle?~
@21708 = ~I must take my leave now, Young Ned. Farewell.~
@21709 = ~Oh, I know bits and pieces. Haven't heard much good gossip lately, but I can tell ye that the Three D's be rubbin' Emmerich's fur the wrong way recently.~
@21710 = ~"Three D's"?~
@21711 = ~~
@21712 = ~Aye! He's me mother's brother. And he be the feistiest bastard and the toughest sailor in these parts. Least, he used to be. How's the old piece o' sun-baked whale blubber doing these days, anyhow?~
@21713 = ~To tell the truth, he's an old drunk wasting away in his hut.~
@21714 = ~He's doing just fine.~
@21715 = ~I should really be going now, Young Ned. Farewell.~
@21716 = ~Oh, that be Selara. Thom named her after his dear dead wife. She aren't done yet, though. When Thom finishes her, I can take ye out on the lake. The other boats are all just too small, see?~
@21717 = ~Thanks, Young Ned. Farewell.~
@21718 = ~Oh, that be Selara. Thom named her after his dear dead wife. He just finished her up recently. If ye want, I can take ye out on the lake in her.~
@21719 = ~Actually, Young Ned, could you take me to the Burial Isle?~
@21720 = ~~
@21721 = ~Not right now. Farewell.~
@21722 = ~Aye. Dingbat, Dumbbutt, and... whatever that other one be called. They be thugs, the worst kind o' scum. Emmerich knows they be up to no good. Only a matter o' time, says I.~
@21723 = ~Oh... *sob*... that... *sob* makes me... just about the proudest nephew in Icewind Dale. Umberlee willing, I hope I be half that drunk when I turn old.~
@21724 = ~~
@21725 = ~Aye... that shiftless, lazy bastard! Once was a time me uncle could down five tankards of southern rum, cut a man from gut to gullet, and wrestle a kraken to the depths o' the sea all in the same day.~
@21726 = ~~
@21727 = ~Aye! Wait, no! *choke* *sputter* What ye be wantin' to go out there for?! Only the dead be on that isle, and they aren't moved on just yet, if ye get me meanin'.~
