@21885 = ~You're Hailee's mother?~
@21886 = ~I arrived only recently... and the journey was a difficult one. I've come because of the barbarian threat.~
@21887 = ~How long have you been drinking?~
@21888 = ~I must take my leave, Ambere. Farewell.~
@21889 = ~Tybald's wife...?! Ha! I sleep under his roof at times, but am I his *wife*? In name only... Ha! May his innards freeze and his body be buried in one of his barrels...~
@21890 = ~You sound like you bear little love for your husband.~
@21891 = ~I... see. Can you tell me anything of the barbarian threat?~
@21892 = ~~
@21893 = ~I bear NO love for that scarecrow of a man. He dragged me here, to the North, to NOWHERE, so he could try to make a few coppers, and I could freeze and die... what a *fool* I was.~
@21894 = ~If your life here is such a burden, why don't you leave?~
@21895 = ~I don't think I can help you with your family... can you tell me anything of the barbarian threat?~
@21896 = ~~
@21897 = ~You think I haven't *tried*?! What do YOU know—the caravans aren't running now, and every man I bed promises to take me south... then leaves me here...~
@21898 = ~We haven't the patience for your silly questions, girl. We've just been shipwrecked. Tell us about this village. We understood the village to be uninhabited.~
@21899 = ~Are you willing to get away from your family and this town so much you would give your body to a stranger?~
@21900 = ~And how many more do you plan to bed to leave here?~
@21901 = ~~
@21902 = ~~
@21903 = ~I would sleep with a *garrison* if it meant warmer climes and an escape from this frigid hell.~
@21904 = ~Have you no *shame*, woman?! What happened to drive you to such a state?~
@21905 = ~Hmmm. If you have a room where we could be alone, then perhaps we can come to an arrangement.~
@21906 = ~Your weakness *sickens* me. If you would escape, then you should have the strength to do so. If not, you deserve your fate.~
@21907 = ~~
@21908 = ~My husband, that fool, Tybald, brought us here to the North, promising a "bright new future." Now years have passed, yet he *still* labors in his shop. My daughter is a wild thing... more wolf than girl.~
@21909 = ~This is NOT what I wished of my life, and I would do anything to leave it and start anew.~
@21910 = ~So you have decided to become every man's thing in the hopes they can promise you something more? You are truly a fool to surrender yourself twice.~
@21911 = ~Your presence here only harms your family... you should leave at once. They will survive, and most likely prosper, without you.~
@21912 = ~Then you are the one who must change your life... and looking for others to change it will only dig you deeper.~
@21913 = ~~
@21914 = ~But... there are no caravans... I can't go alone... perhaps I... could leave with you? I'd be no trouble, I'd... I could... I just couldn't leave by myself...~
@21915 = ~My heart bleeds for you—you would gladly leave your family alone, but you cannot bear to be alone yourself? If you truly want to leave, then find the strength and *do* so.~
@21916 = ~I can't help you. I'm here about the barbarian threat, nothing more.~
@21917 = ~If I were in your position, I would at least make the attempt. Farewell, Ambere.~
@21918 = ~How *dare* you raise your voice to me?! You—I should—I... I *will* leave, then. I'll leave this filthy little town and prove you wrong!~
@21919 = ~That is all I ask. Farewell, Ambere.~
@21920 = ~Y... You don't know what it is like...~
@21921 = ~You have an honest husband that does honest work, a beautiful daughter, and a home far removed from the mess of cities to the south, and you claim you *suffer*?~
@21922 = ~I have no desire to speak of this anymore. I'm here about the barbarian threat, nothing more.~
@21923 = ~Granted, I do not... but if I were in your position, I would at least try to improve my situation. Farewell, Ambere.~
@21924 = ~You talk nonsense... my husband makes coppers, barely enough to save from month to month, and my daughter is wilder than the barbarians...~
@21925 = ~So your husband makes enough to save, and your daughter has the strength of a barbarian... how can you spit on such blessings? Go to your family; they need you, and you need them.~
@21926 = ~I... it is too *late* for such things. Too much damage has been done...~
@21927 = ~Your place is with your family... it is *not* too late. Find your strength and go to them.~
@21928 = ~I... will try.~
@21929 = ~Hailee? That thrice-damned girl! Can't a day go by without that brat getting herself into trouble?! Entirely too much of her idiot father in her...~
@21930 = ~I met Hailee by the town well... your son is trapped inside the well and needs your help.~
@21931 = ~"Thrice-damned"? Hailee is *your* daughter, isn't she?~
@21932 = ~Never mind. What can you tell me of the barbarian threat to Lonelywood?~
@21933 = ~~
@21934 = ~~
@21935 = ~Oh, my *son*? Ha! Fell hard for one of her little lies, did you?~
