@24336 = ~Be thinkin' to creep up on a blind old dwarf, are ye? Don't think I don't know ye're there—I can hear ye breathing, so speak up.~
@24337 = ~~
@24338 = ~I be Tiernon, of the Clan Hearthstone. Who be ye?~
@24339 = ~Wait a moment... Tiernon Denthelm, the famous dwarven weaponsmith?~
@24340 = ~Tiernon? Tales from the Hearthstone Clan said you'd vanished. What are you doing in this glacier?~
@24341 = ~I thought the Hearthstone Clan had settled near the Sunset Mountains.~
@24342 = ~Godhood~
@24343 = ~What happened to your eyes?~
@24344 = ~Have ye come to harm her? If ye have, ye'll be gettin' no help from me. Get ye gone an' trouble us no more.~
@24345 = ~We have no desire to harm her; we came in search of information.~
@24346 = ~We will not harm her unless she forces our hand, dwarf. We have come for information, nothing more.~
@24347 = ~Hmn. Yer words ring true to me ears, but I trust not a face I can't see—an' she don't want to speak to ye anyway, so there's little help to be had.~
@24348 = ~Why doesn't she want to see us?~
@24349 = ~We have to see her, whether she desires the meeting or not, dwarf. Now tell me where she is hiding.~
@24350 = ~Ye're *why* she's hiding here, stranger. She told me ye'd come... an' ye'd be carrying her death with ye.~
@24351 = ~She's been afraid o' yer visit for a ten-year or more, so much so she won't step outside her cave. It's been all I can do to get her to eat.~
@24352 = ~Why would we kill her?~
@24353 = ~We have no reason to kill the Seer, dwarf.~
@24354 = ~I can't see yer face, stranger, much less read yer heart. Ye could have a score o' reasons.~
@24355 = ~If the Seer predicted our coming, she must have surely predicted we would speak to her.~
@24356 = ~If we had come to kill the Seer, then surely we would have killed anyone else in our way... like a blind dwarf, perhaps?~
@24357 = ~Hmnn. I see yer point, stranger. All right then, I'll help ye—but if ye bring any harm to her, ye'll answer to me.~
@24358 = ~She's sealed herself within a chamber below, an' the door's a special one, one o' me own making. There's no way to open it unless ye know how to *look* at it.~
@24359 = ~Ye need to see the reflection o' the door in a mirror, then ye'll see the workings of it. A finely crafted thing it is, make no mistake.~
@24360 = ~Where do we get a mirror?~
@24361 = ~I can craft ye one, but I'll need yer help with it—there are times I need a spare set o' eyes to finish a piece.~
@24362 = ~All right, then. Where do we begin?~
@24363 = ~That's the spirit! Now, go to the table an' grab the two smallest o' the three chisels ye see, then...~
@24364 = ~There ye be—that'll serve ye as a key to see her, if ye're determined to. Now get along with ye, an' watch yerself in these caves.~
@24365 = ~Tiernon... what are you doing here?~
@24366 = ~~
@24367 = ~So you can craft a mirror from ice... can you craft a rose?~
@24368 = ~Before I go, is this dented shield yours?~
@24369 = ~It's been a long journey, Tiernon. Do you have any supplies?~
@24370 = ~Farewell, Tiernon.~
