This spell creates two 11-HD shambling mounds. These creatures willingly aid the caster in combat or whatever other duties they are assigned and have the capability to carry out.~
@24914 = ~Unholy Word
(Conjuration)

Level: 7
Sphere: Combat
Range: 0
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius
Saving Throw: None

When uttered, this spell turns the priest into a bridge between <PRO_HISHER> deity and the Prime Material Plane, allowing <PRO_HIMHER> to funnel magical energy to smite all creatures of good alignment in the area of effect. The effects differ depending on the target's Hit Dice:

– Fewer than 4: Death
– 4 to 7: Stunned for 1 turn
– 8 to 11: Slowed for 1 turn with a 75% chance of spell failure
– 12 and up: Deafened for 1 turn with a 50% chance of spell failure

There is no Saving Throw; the effects are instantaneous and last for the duration of the spell or until dispelled. Unholy Word can only be cast by evil-aligned priests.~
@24915 = ~Sunfire
(Invocation)

Level: 5
Range: 0
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius
Saving Throw: 1/2

A sunfire is like a fireball—an explosive burst of flame that delivers damage proportional to the level of the wizard who cast it. Sunfire deals 1d6 points of fire damage for each caster level, up to a maximum of 15d6. The wizard gestures with <PRO_HISHER> hand and the entire area around <PRO_HIMHER> erupts in flames, striking all except for the caster. Creatures failing their Saves vs. Spell suffer full damage from the blast. Those who roll successful Saving Throws manage to dodge, fall flat, or roll aside, each receiving half damage.~
@24916 = ~::This scenery is depressing. Too bad I'll have to look at it for so long when you *die*.::~
@24917 = ~::Could you please put me back in my sheath? I'm scared. Oooh! So scared!::~
@24918 = ~::We're going to die. Why don't you just put me down and go take up the plow?::~
@24919 = ~::Why must you insist on carrying me exposed to the world?::~
@24920 = ~::Oh, for Solonor's sake, you don't even know how to hold a sword properly.::~
@24921 = ~::Would you mind throwing me into a nearby lake? I'd rather keep the fish company.::~
@24922 = ~::If we get into a fight, be sure to put the pointy end into the enemy. That gets 'em every time!::~
@24923 = ~::Hey, halfwit, why don't you do us both a favor and put me back where you found me?::~
@24924 = ~::If my mother only saw me now... but if she saw you, she'd probably cry herself into oblivion.::~
@24925 = ~::I'm tired. Sleepy sword.::~
@24926 = ~::Why did it have to be Icewind Dale?! Why?! I could be with a soldier in Evermeet right now.::~
@24927 = ~::I have a special purpose: to be dropped and left alone while you go off and die.::~
@24928 = ~::Oooh! Good one! A few dozen more hits and maybe we'll be getting somewhere!::~
@24929 = ~::You're incompetent. A *skilled* warrior would kill his opponent much faster. Seriously.::~
@24930 = ~::Your technique is all wrong. *sigh* You're hopeless.::~
@24931 = ~::Hmm. Not bad! Actually, I'm lying. That was a horrible maneuver.::~
@24932 = ~::I'm not sure which stinks more, your hand or your martial prowess.::~
@24933 = ~::Mmm. Warrior good! Hit enemy! Magic sword! Me dumb! Urk! Urk!::~
@24934 = ~::Did you see a little girl back there? I think she has grandchildren now because that's how long it's been since you've hurt someone.::~
@24935 = ~::There's bad and then there's *bad*. You're worse.::~
@24936 = ~::There are many great heroes in Faerûn. You... are destined to fall beneath their blades.::~
@24937 = ~::I've seen old blind peasants cut wheat with better swings than that.::~
@24938 = ~::Friend, we're not chopping wood here. There's a bit of *finesse* required when you use a sword.::~
@24939 = ~~
@24940 = ~::Amazing. The last time my wielder made an attack that sloppy, they were disemboweled. You're lucky.::~
@24941 = ~"Bwahaha! As if I would allow some pig-ape to wear me without being molested! DIE!"~
@24942 = ~"Muhahaha! Simple pig-ape. I told you it was safe to *wear* me, not safe to *summon* me!"~
@24943 = ~"This is my last act of service to you, pig. I'll see you in the Abyss!"~
@24944 = ~"Not so fast, my sisters."~
@24945 = ~"What are you doing in my kitchen? Guards!"~
@24946 = ~So... You dared to follow me here. I think you will find that to be a fatal mistake.~ [ICAS001]
@24947 = ~Fatal only to you, Icasaracht.~
@24948 = ~I have no intention of fighting you. Let me leave this place, and there'll be no need for any bloodshed.~
@24949 = ~Spoken like a true hero. Shall we put those words to the test?~ [ICAS002]
@24950 = ~Wait, I'm curious. Returning here made it easy to find you. Why did you do it?~
@24951 = ~Before we do, there is something I would know. Why do you hate the Ten Towns so much?~
@24952 = ~Yes. Let's end this senseless banter. Prepare to die!~
@24953 = ~I feared as much, but I had little choice. It was a calculated risk.~ [ICAS003]
@24954 = ~To what end?~
@24955 = ~To cheat death itself! To be born anew as you see me now! Only by returning here could I do this.~ [ICAS004]
@24956 = ~Why did you need to return here?~
@24957 = ~When I built this lair, I included two special wards. One would serve as a beacon that would allow my spirit to find its way here upon my death, and the other would preserve a body almost indefinitely.~ [ICAS005]
@24958 = ~I then reared two offspring, devoid of their spirits, and placed their bodies in the preservation wards.~ [ICAS006]
@24959 = ~The plan was simple. If I were to die, my spirit would return here and find a new body in which to live again.~ [ICAS007]
@24960 = ~How did you rear young with no spirits?~
@24961 = ~Let me ask you something else. Why do you hate the Ten Towns so much?~
@24962 = ~I've heard enough of your evil. Prepare to die.~
@24963 = ~A brilliant plan, but it will not save you. Prepare to die!~
@24964 = ~While their flesh was yet unformed, I warded the eggs so that no spirit could find a home within them.~ [ICAS008]
@24965 = ~That was a terrible thing to do to your own offspring, Icasaracht.~
@24966 = ~Ingenious... though I daresay some would find what you did questionable.~
@24967 = ~Would you rather I had bore them normally and then stripped their spirits from them? No, by doing what I did they were nothing more than empty shells, ready for use.~ [ICAS009]
@24968 = ~I understand what you did and why you did it, but that does not make it right.~
@24969 = ~You found an interesting solution to the problem of mortality, but it still feels wrong somehow.~
@24970 = ~Unfortunately, their father felt as you do and objected to my plan. Had he agreed to it, he could have shared immortality with me...~ [ICAS010]
@24971 = ~I take it that's his skeleton in the Field of Bones?~
@24972 = ~Yes... He attacked me and had to be slain. I regret... but it had to be...~ [ICAS011]
