@24976 = ~Ages ago, dragonkind roamed Faerûn freely. Then the *civilized* races came to power and began to encroach upon our lands.~ [ICAS012]
@24977 = ~Bloody wars were fought in which your kind launched entire armies upon us. Against such numbers, even we soon fell.~ [ICAS013]
@24978 = ~Now we are solitary creatures who hide in caves in far away lands. We fear sleep, for it is often the sleep of death if we are discovered!~ [ICAS014]
@24979 = ~What does this have to do with the Ten Towns?~
@24980 = ~I've heard enough of this. Prepare to die!~
@24981 = ~I couldn't care less about any of this. Prepare to die!~
@24982 = ~I was slain fighting for my homeland against an invading army. Aihonen, a man of the Ten Towns, wielded the blade that broke my heart...~ [ICAS015]
@24983 = ~An invading army? History paints a different picture, Icasaracht.~
@24984 = ~Yes, and history is written by the victors as they say. It is also said that history repeats itself...~ [ICAS016]
@24985 = ~~
@24986 = ~Look at the plight of the barbarians. Even now they are being driven from their lands by the Ten Towns.~ [ICAS017]
@24987 = ~Soon they will be left with two choices: extinction or absorption. They are a proud people and will not bend. They will choose extinction.~ [ICAS018]
@24988 = ~An entire culture will vanish, lost forever, all in the name of civilization... Just as my culture has been lost...~ [ICAS019]
@24989 = ~I find it hard to believe that you were doing this out of altruism.~
@24990 = ~~
