@24992 = ~[NULL NODE]~
@24993 = ~When I awakened from my sleep, I looked upon the world anew. And I was shocked to see how little had changed.~ [ICAS021]
@24994 = ~My lands were still in the hands of the Ten Towns. The plight of the barbarians had not changed at all.~ [ICAS022]
@24995 = ~I saw a kindred spirit in Wylfdene, so I joined with him to end this tragedy once and for all.~ [ICAS023]
@24996 = ~Tell me something else. You were slain almost a century ago. Why did it take so long for you to awaken?~
@24997 = ~~
@24998 = ~~
@24999 = ~The sword of Aihonen had a special enchantment, almost an intelligence of its own. When the fatal blow was struck, it somehow knew that I would be born anew.~ [ICAS024]
@25000 = ~The blade broke, sacrificing itself, that I might be trapped. My spirit lay within my shattered heart at the bottom of Lac Dinneshere.~ [ICAS025]
@25001 = ~I can only guess that the blade was removed, allowing my spirit to go free...~ [ICAS026]
@25002 = ~I now hold the sword of Aihonen. It has been forged anew.~
@25003 = ~I now hold the sword of Aihonen. It has been forged anew and now sings with a life of its own.~
@25004 = ~Yes... I sensed the blade when you first entered here and was concerned. However, I now see that the original enchantment was not restored. It is of no consequence.~ [ICAS027]
@25005 = ~Icasaracht, I'd rather we came to some sort of agreement than fight. Can we do this?~
@25006 = ~The time for talk is over, Icasaracht. You must die unless you agree to leave the Ten Towns in peace. Can you do that?~
@25007 = ~Never! My heart was shattered long ago and all mercy bled from the wound.~ [ICAS028]
@25008 = ~I lost my love, my life, and my kingdom. I shall reclaim it all, or I will pass into oblivion like most of my kind.~ [ICAS029]
@25009 = ~Draw your blade. Let us end this now...~ [ICAS030]
@25010 = ~~
@25011 = ~I think not. I believe you will find the door has sealed behind you... Shall we put an end to this?~ [ICAS031]
