@25562 = ~Drop the act, Baldemar. We know you're involved in this.~
@25563 = ~Wylfdene had the one-eyed delegate executed. Before he died, he confessed to being a hired assassin.~
@25564 = ~Then why send a delegate to negotiate peace? No, I believe Wylfdene was telling the truth.~
@25565 = ~I trust no one... least of all shifty bureaucrats that hide behind assassins.~
@25566 = ~Perhaps you're right. Let me ask you about something else.~
@25567 = ~We'll see. After we've dealt with the barbarian threat, I intend to bring this matter before the council.~
@25568 = ~Look, you spineless worm... you'll tell us what we want to know, or I'll cut out your lying tongue and beat you to death with it.~
@25569 = ~You're right... we can't prove it. But from now on we'll be keeping a close eye on you. Farewell.~
@25570 = ~Go on. We're listening.~
@25571 = ~We believe you, Baldemar. However, you are not entirely blameless. You should've had the courage to stand up for what is right... even if it cost you your seat on the council.~
@25572 = ~All right, we'll let you off the hook this time. But if we find out you've lied to us again...~
@25573 = ~Not only are you a poor liar, you're a weak and pathetic excuse for a man. Now, get out of my sight!~
@25574 = ~It's not too late to do the right thing. You are, after all, still this town's duly elected representative to the council.~
@25575 = ~Maybe next time you'll know better. Farewell.~
@25576 = ~You're welcome, Baldemar. Farewell.~
@25577 = ~Very well, we'll be going then. Try to stay out of trouble... or else we'll make sure they bury you alongside your mother.~
