@26723 = ~Summon Chalimandren~
@26724 = ~Fetid air fills your nostrils as the restless dead of the Burial Isle discover your camp.~
@26725 = ~~
@26726 = ~A cold wind awakens you as undead barbarians shamble towards camp.~
@26727 = ~"Death and Drek," you exclaim, as your rest is interrupted by attacking frost salamanders.~
@26728 = ~You have saved the northern lands from the threat of Icasaracht.~
@26729 = ~Time... within its swirling mists lies the knowledge of all things... past and future... endings and beginnings.~
@26730 = ~It is all here, hidden from view... waiting to be revealed to those who have eyes to see.~
@26731 = ~Far to the north, beyond the wind-swept peaks of the Spine of the World, beyond the realms of men who call themselves civilized, dwell a people whose way of life is built upon the gift of Sight.~
@26732 = ~Among the tribes of the Uthgardt, the visions of a shaman serve to guide his people through the fog of an uncertain future.~
@26733 = ~So it was with Hjollder, elder and shaman to the Tribe of the Bear.~
@26734 = ~For it was his visions that foretold the return of a slain king, awakened from the halls of death by a spirit consumed by vengeance.~
@26735 = ~His vision carried him across the tundra, to a place where men built their homes beneath an ancient oak with branches that stretched skywards to embrace the clouds.~
@26736 = ~It is here that his vision showed him the faces of the strangers that would journey far across a sea of ice and snow.~
@26737 = ~With the death of Icasaracht's spirit, centuries of hate were at long last put to rest.~
@26738 = ~The tribes of the North and the people of the Ten Towns sheathed their weapons and resumed their uneasy watchfulness of each other... it was a peace of sorts, for as long as peace ever lasts.~
@26739 = ~Wylfdene's body was returned to the Burial Isle. With his return, the wailing of the virgins fell silent... and they slept beneath the earth, with their king, once again.~
@26740 = ~And of those brave ones that came to defend the North? What of you?~
@26741 = ~As I look upon you all, I see you as you once were, as you will be, branching out to glittering futures.~
@26742 = ~Though I need not say more of your future. For all that I spoken of, all that I have seen, shall be revealed to you... in time.~
@26743 = ~They say that history is the greatest of all teachers. And that tales of past deeds define who we are in the present, and what we shall be in the future.~
@26744 = ~I shall tell you of such a tale. It is a tale quite familiar to me, for I have spent nearly a lifetime piecing it together and chronicling it here within this book.~
@26745 = ~Our story takes place in the northern region of Faerûn known as Icewind Dale. It is a harsh, frozen land, cut off from the rest of world by a wall of jagged peaks called the Spine of the World.~
@26746 = ~For centuries, the icy plains of the dale have been home to the barbarian peoples of the Uthgardt and Reghedmen.~
@26747 = ~Huddled together in small, closely knit tribes, the barbarians lived simple lives: free, proud, and fiercely independent.~
@26748 = ~Until the day an archmage named Arakon came to Icewind Dale.~
@26749 = ~With an army of mercenaries, Arakon sought to conquer the North and force the fierce barbarians into slavery.~
@26750 = ~Long weeks of battle followed, and the scattered barbarian tribes suffered terrible losses. Defeat seemed inevitable.~
@26751 = ~In their darkest hour, a barbarian shaman named Jerrod came forth and demanded a council between all of the remaining tribes of the north.~
@26752 = ~Welther~
@26753 = ~Welther~
@26754 = ~Priest of Talos~
@26755 = ~Priest of Talos~
@26756 = ~Strengthened by a new sense of purpose, the barbarians rallied behind their new leader.~
@26757 = ~Wave after wave of barbarian warriors tore into Arakon's hired army, forcing them on the defensive, and ultimately, into full retreat.~
@26758 = ~As his army crumbled around him, Arakon had time for one last, desperate act before his enemies descended upon him.~
@26759 = ~The foolish archmage's cries of victory immediately turned to shrieks of terror as the hideous and twisted shapes of demonkind materialized from the portal and poured onto the battlefield.~
@26760 = ~The sudden appearance of the demons drove the combatants, barbarian and mercenary alike, to turn to meet the new threat, side by side.~
@26761 = ~As his people fell around him, the barbarian shaman, Jerrod, looked up from the blood-drenched snow of the battlefield and caught sight of a lone figure high upon a ridge in the distance.~
@26762 = ~Jerrod immediately recognized this vision as an omen from his god, Tempos. And in that instant, he knew what had to be done.~
@26763 = ~Shouting cries to his god, he charged through the ranks of the demons and plunged into the portal.~
@26764 = ~As Jerrod's blood fused with the energies of the portal, an explosion of white light engulfed the battlefield. When the light subsided, the demons were gone and the portal was closed.~
@26765 = ~In its place hovered a disk of solid stone. Frozen within the center of the disk was Jerrod's body, locked in his final moment of agony... in his final moment of triumph... for all eternity.~
@26766 = ~But that is not the end of our tale... It is... but the beginning.~
@26767 = ~So it was that the patchwork militia set off from Easthaven, bound for the troubled village of Kuldahar with the party of strangers in tow.~
@26768 = ~You are too far away from the grave to do anything with it.~
@26769 = ~On they traveled, across the windswept tundra of the Dale, through the foothills of the Spine of the World, and upwards on the steep and treacherous trails of the Kuldahar Pass.~
@26770 = ~Eager to seek out the evil that threatened the Pass, they did not expect it to find them first. High upon the cliffs of the Pass, a band of frost giants had prepared an ambush.~
@26771 = ~Hurling boulders and dislodging massive outcroppings of rock and snow, the giants sparked an avalanche that thundered down the mountainside and crashed down upon the heads of the unsuspecting expedition.~
@26772 = ~Nearby, you see an open grave. A chill runs up your spine as you hear a sound emit from it. You shake your head and continue walking. The sound is clearer now. You are not imagining it. Muffled cries for help are coming from the grave.~
@26773 = ~The grave is only partially filled. The gravekeeper must be lazy. Within a few minutes you have reached the coffin. You open it to find a corpse and a man who is quite obviously alive. You help him out of the coffin.~
@26774 = ~Those fortunate enough to survive the avalanche pulled themselves free of the mountain of snow and bodies that now barred the way back to Easthaven.~
@26775 = ~Freed from the shackles of his tormented mind, the cursed elven lord was at last able to assist the heroes in their quest.~
@26776 = ~With the artifact raised before him, clutched tightly in his skeletal hands, the undead sorcerer peered intently into the Gem as he whispered a series of strange chants and incantations.~
@26777 = ~A spark of light briefly flashed within the Gem, as if a ray of sunlight had caught upon its surface.~
@26778 = ~In the heat of the battle, the twisted priest of Ilmater stumbled, gripping his chest as if mortally stricken.~
@26779 = ~Other than a rotting corpse there is nothing of note within the grave.~
@26780 = ~A faint glow began to emanate from the crystal that hung around his neck. Suddenly, the entire cave was engulfed in an explosion of blinding light.~
@26781 = ~When the light finally died, the party discovered that they were no longer within the dark passages of Dorn's Deep.~
@26782 = ~But this was not the sleepy fishing village they had left so long ago.~
