@26798 = ~For years, I have pondered its passages, studying every line, committing each word to memory. Perhaps now, in the telling of it, I shall at last find the answers I seek.~
@26799 = ~Heart of Winter~
@26800 = ~And suddenly, reflected within the mirrored facets of the stone, there appeared an image of a statue. The statue was clearly a monument of sorts, depicting an elf and a dwarf sitting side by side on a dual throne.~
@26801 = ~To the frozen north these heroes would come, drawn into a twisted maze of shared destinies that would lead us all into the cold and terrible Heart of Winter.~
@26802 = ~Tales follow you, and tales await you, as they always do for those whose hearts yearn for adventure and glory.~
@26803 = ~It is said that such tales shall, with each telling, illuminate us all with the light of truth.~
@26804 = ~A respected warrior, Jerrod persuaded the council to put aside their differences and unite against Arakon.~
@26805 = ~The combined might of the Northmen proved more than a match for Arakon, who had counted on the division of the tribes.~
@26806 = ~The remaining warriors bravely charged the portal to drive the hellspawn back... and were slaughtered by the hundreds.~
@26807 = ~Battered and disheartened by the loss of their comrades, the survivors had little choice but to continue on to Kuldahar... alone.~
@26808 = ~Handing over the Heartstone Gem, the party stood back and watched Larrel begin his divination.~
@26809 = ~As they struggled to regain their bearings, they realized that they had been returned to the town of Easthaven.~
@26810 = ~tormented by the memory of his mistakes, and waiting for the day he would return to Faerûn and exact his revenge.~
