@34947 = ~Press the icon in the upper right to access the world map.~
@34948 = ~The world map is updated as you are informed of new locations.~
@34949 = ~Clerics can cast divine spells granted to them by their god.~
@34950 = ~They can restore Hit Points with healing spells, such as Cure Light Wounds.~
@34951 = ~Clerics can also summon minions.~
@34952 = ~Clerics have the ability to Turn Undead, which will cause undead creatures to flee or be destroyed.~
@34953 = ~Thieves have a variety of useful adventuring skills.~
@34954 = ~Open Locks is the most useful ability—it allows you to open locked doors or containers.~
@34955 = ~Locks can sometimes be opened through bashing.~
@34956 = ~Thieves can pick pockets, which lets them steal gold or useful items from their targets.~
@34957 = ~Thieves can also Hide in Shadows, which allows them to move undetected.~
@34958 = ~While hidden, a Thief can scout or backstab an enemy for a damage bonus.~
@34959 = ~Move characters by pressing them and then pressing on the ground.~
@34960 = ~You can order each party member around separately.~
@34961 = ~Blue circles are neutral. To speak to a neutral target, press on it.~
@34962 = ~Red circles are hostile. To attack a hostile target, press it.~
@34963 = ~By default, characters will attack any hostile targets they see.~
@34964 = ~To travel between areas, press on doors or map edges. Be sure to gather your party before venturing forth! ~
@34965 = ~To open containers, such as treasure chests or drawers, press on them.~
@34966 = ~You can take items from containers, or put items within them.~
@34967 = ~Mages, Bards and Sorcerers cast arcane spells. Mages and Bards must find new spell scrolls, while Sorcerers learn magic as they level up.~
@34968 = ~To cast a spell at a target, select the spell from the spell list and then press on your target.~
@34969 = ~Spellcasters can summon allies on the battlefield through certain spells.~
@34970 = ~It's important to use defensive spells that prevent attackers from harming your spellcasters, as they are typically weak in close combat.~
@34971 = ~This button allows you to speak with someone.~
@34972 = ~These are your Quick Weapon slots. Press one to select that weapon, press twice to use it on someone.~
@34973 = ~To the right are your special abilities, and any items you have placed in your Quick Item slots.~
@34974 = ~The Quick Loot bar is activated with this red gem.~
