@34977 = ~HOW TO PLAY~
@34978 = ~Spellcasters are vulnerable to physical attacks. Keep them out of melee combat.~
@34979 = ~Some spells do damage, others make enemies less effective. There are also spells that enhance your party members, making them stronger.~
@34980 = ~At the outset of battle, be sure to cast as many spells that enhance your party as you can.~
@34981 = ~Hang your magic users back, and have them hit the enemy with magic. Magic Missile is a great first spell to learn for this.~
@34982 = ~Pause often to reassess the situation and assign new targets to your party members.~
@34983 = ~Some spells impact a large area. Position your party to avoid being hit by friendly fire.~
@34984 = ~Disable enemies to make a fight more fair. Spells such as Sleep, Cloudkill, and Hold Person are excellent for this purpose.~
@34985 = ~There are many different kinds of melee combat characters. Fighters, Paladins, Clerics, Druids, and others can fill this role with the proper equipment.~
@34986 = ~While in combat, protect your spellcasters from attackers with your melee characters. ~
@34987 = ~Pause often to reassess the situation and assign new targets to your party members.~
@34988 = ~You can block doorways to prevent your weaker or ranged party members from being reached.~
@34989 = ~Be sure to keep an eye on the Hit Points of your characters—they can drop quickly in the heat of battle.~
@34990 = ~A useful tactic is to pepper the enemy with ranged shots before switching to a melee weapon and moving into close combat.~
