@35373 = ~I do not want a wish now.~
@35374 = ~Standing before you is a djinni of immense power, the air thick with electricity around it. It regards you coolly. "Greetings to you, spellweaver. Are you ready to begin negotiations?"~
@35375 = ~The djinni grins widely, winking at you. "Perhaps the wisest of courses, spellweaver. Very well... it shall be as you wish."~
@35376 = ~The being pauses a moment, surprised, before chuckling with amusement. "We are between moments here, spellcaster. Time has no bearing on you and me while we speak; have no worry."~
@35377 = ~"The spell you have cast is an attempt to temporarily control vast cosmic power. It is unstable and therefore only truly useful in combat events... unless you have years to devote to the formulation of your wish, of course."~
@35378 = ~"It is that formulation that requires negotiation." The djinni pulls a quill and a paper scroll from the air, grinning. "Since you do not have years to waste, you will attempt to describe to me what you desire from your wish."~
@35379 = ~"And I," here the djinni looks pleased, "will use my vast intelligence to distort your purpose as I please. Don't feel bad... the forces at work here are such that it is not often that one gets what one truly hopes for."~
@35380 = ~"But you can certainly try. The wise often do well... and you spellweavers are often quite wise, yes?" It taps its quill thoughtfully on its head. "Do you wish to begin, then?"~
@35381 = ~The djinni nods. "As you say." Quickly, the two of you begin negotiating a complex contract. The djinni is tricky, carefully attempting to twist your meaning with words, legal phrases, and clauses that you can barely understand...~
@35382 = ~Fortunately, you are quick to catch on. Before long, you begin tricking the djinni's phrasings yourself, leaving it quite frustrated. You still doubt you'll get what you want, but chances are the djinni won't be able to trick you.~
@35383 = ~You are wise enough to keep pace with the djinni, preventing the being from taking total advantage of you. Still... the contract is hard to understand, and you wonder at the end result.~
@35384 = ~Throughout the process, the djinni continues to baffle you... and you are not even sure if your desired wish will be similar to your original premise. At best, you stall the worst of the clauses.~
@35385 = ~Your lack of wisdom leaves you at a complete disadvantage. Throughout the writing of the contract, the djinni all but bullies you mentally into a position of watching him all but write the complex document on his own... there are few objections you can make.~
@35386 = ~The contract complete, the djinni dons a pair of spectacles and looks it over with an arched brow. "Very well, spellcaster. I can interpret the items listed here in the following ways. Choose carefully which you would prefer."~
@35387 = ~I am ready.~
@35388 = ~Negotiations? What do you mean?~
@35389 = ~I don't have time to negotiate in the middle of combat!~
@35390 = ~No, I have changed my mind. Return to whence you came.~
@35391 = ~Then explain to me what you meant by negotiations.~
@35392 = ~Then let us begin.~
@35393 = ~Never mind. Return to where you came from, djinni.~
@35394 = ~But we don't have time to do all this in the middle of combat!~
@35395 = ~Yes, let's begin.~
@35396 = ~No, I have changed my mind. Return to whence you came.~
