Type: One-handed
Requires:
 11 Strength

Weight: 7~
@39464 = ~To enchant a katana is no simple process. Unlike conventional weapons, the katana is already a near-perfect fighting sword. To improve it usually requires a sacrifice, perhaps a dying samurai might beg a Wu Jen to infuse his fighting spirit into the spirit of the katana. The wielder of an enchanted katana, such as this one, must respect the customs of Kara-Tur and of the samurai who once carried this blade into battle. Not doing so could drastically change one's luck for the worse.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +1
Damage: 1d10+1 (slashing)
Speed Factor: 3
Proficiency Type: Katana
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 6 Strength

Weight: 5~
@39465 = ~This sleek katana radiates magical energy when carried. The Malakar, or "Dueling Steel," was used by a less-than-honorable samurai during duels against other samurai. As if of its own volition, it will swoop down and deflect the slashing attacks of other weapons. It is perfect for the warrior concerned about defense as well as offense.

