@39634 = ~The simplest of staff weapons is the quarterstaff, a length of wood six to nine feet in length. High-quality quarterstaves are made of stout oak and are shod with metal at both ends. Powerful enchantments during the making of this staff have improved its accuracy and the damage it can cause, but they bear no signature.

